        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>BARCELONA • Lionel Messi has no plans to be­come a coach when he re­tires from play­ing, say­ing he is more in­ter­ested in be­ing a di­rec­tor of foot­ball than work­ing in the un­for­giv­ing world of man­age­ment.</p>
    <p>The Ar­gen­tinian for­ward added that even if he leaves Barcelona when his con­tract ex­pires in six months, his 20-year ca­reer at the Nou Camp was still a “story of love” and “it should not stain what I’ve lived in my ca­reer”.</p>
    <p>The 33-year-old Barcelona cap­tain also said he would like to work for the Cata­lan gi­ants in some ca­pac­ity after he re­tires.</p>


